premise_source_doc_sentence: Instead , the new station was granted 90.1 MHz with an effective radiated power of 5 watts  (  non-directional antenna with an effective height above average terrain of -29 metres  )  .

According to the Broadcasting Notice of Consultation for CKAW-FM on January 23 , 2015 , the station was initially licensed to operate at 106.3 MHz with an effective radiated power of 3.2 watts  (  non-directional antenna of 3.2 watts with an effective height of antenna above average terrain of 18.2 metres  )  .
